This paper deals with the combinatorial and geometric properties of point sets in the plane, which are typical topics in computational geometry (cs.CG) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The concept of order type is also related to the study of partially ordered sets, which is a common topic in both cs.DM and computer science theory (cs.CC). Finally, the paper uses techniques from algebraic geometry and topology, which are relevant to the subfield of computational geometry known as algebraic and topological methods (cs.GT).
